    "resource_url": {
      "@id": "https://www.msha.gov/data-and-reports/mine-data-retrieval-system"
    },
    "resource_description": {
      "@value": "In addition to providing metadata for all types of mines across the U.S. the Mine Safety and Health Administration also offers coal and other respirable dust concentration data through the Mine Data Retrieval System (MDRS), which is updated each week. These data are not readily available but can be found from the 'Health Samples' option given in the 'Related Reports Links' table on the 'Mine Information' page that is displayed after searching for a specific mine by name or Mine ID. The ‘Mine Information’ results page can also be found by clicking a Mine ID in the search results Mines list displayed after searching by State, County, or other group criteria. The Health Samples link then shows a table of results for coal and/or dust concentrations (mg/m^3) measured in the collected samples. Other options in the Related Reports Links table include Overview, Inspections, Accidents, and Violations to name a few. Additionally, a table of only Coal concentrations for all U.S. mines is available for download as a single, txt formatted file from the \"Coal Dust Samples\" link shown under the 'Explore MSHA Datasets' section seen at the bottom of the MDRS application."
    },
